findings.suggestion:
Add a second catch for serialization failures, or broaden the existing filter. Recommended approach:

```csharp
catch (Exception ex) when (ex is IOException or UnauthorizedAccessException)
{
    return Data.FromError(new ServiceError(ex.Message, "IOError", 500));
}
catch (Exception ex) when (ex is System.Text.Json.JsonException or NotSupportedException)
{
    return Data.FromError(new ServiceError(ex.Message, "SerializationError", 500));
}
```

Also add a test: `Save_NonSerializableObject_ReturnsSerializationError` that passes a circular reference or object with unsupported types.
